Migration of templates with box type fails when the variable is inside a table as the character '|' is interpreted as the column separator rather than the separator between the variable name and the parameters.

For example, this wiki markup template:
{noformat}| *Enter field:* | @VAR_NAME|textarea(1,50)@ |{noformat}

Is migrated to something like:
{quote}| *Enter field:* | @VAR_NAME|textarea(1,50)@ |{quote}

The resultant XHTML is:
{noformat}
<table><tbody> <tr>
  <td><p> <strong>Enter field:</strong> </p></td>
  <td><p> @VAR_NAME</p></td>
  <td><p>textarea(1,50)@ </p></td>
</tr> </tbody></table>
{noformat}

