Currently, when creating a new meeting notes page, the title is in the format *YYYY-MM-DD - Meeting Notes*.

It should be possible to configure the date format to match what the rest of the Confluence instance is set to use.

h3.Steps to Reproduce
# Add a page which contains the character İ in the title. 
# After the page is created, create another page (which is automatically the child page of the page created in step 1)
# You will get the following error:
{quote}
The parent page specified does not exist. It may have been renamed or removed since you started editing.
{quote}

!turkishcharacter.png!

h3.Notes
# This seems to be reproducible only if Confluence is running on JDK 1.7
# This is reproducible if the system locale is set to EN_en:
{code}
-Duser.country=EN -Duser.language=en
{code}

h3.Workaround
Revert back to JDK 1.6 but remove the following folders from the *Confluence Home Directory* before restarting Confluence:
* {{bundled-plugins}}
* {{plugins-cache}}
* {{plugins-osgi-cache}}
* {{plugins-temp}}

